---
id: org.dxos.plugin.file
name: FilePlugin
version: 0.2.0
---

FilePlugin enables DXOS Composer to store and preview binary files — images, videos, and PDFs — as first-class ECHO objects.
A File object's `data` field is a reference to a `Blob` ECHO object (defined in `@dxos/echo`), which abstracts where the
bytes actually live and how they're read. Uploads are routed through a pluggable storage system: the built-in `inline`
storage embeds bytes on the Blob object itself, while external storage (e.g. WNFS, edge) can be contributed by other
plugins by registering a `BlobBackend` on the ECHO Hypergraph. `Blob.url`/`Blob.read` resolve a renderable URL or raw
bytes uniformly regardless of backend, so the File schema and preview surfaces stay backend-agnostic without a
dedicated URL-resolver capability.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`       |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`       |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`       |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`  |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`         |

## Types

```mdl
type File
  desc: ECHO object (typename org.dxos.type.file, version 0.2.0) representing an uploaded binary asset.
  fields:
    name?: string
    type: string             # MIME type
    size: number             # byte count
    data: Ref<Blob>          # reference to a Blob object (org.dxos.type.blob, defined in @dxos/echo)
    timestamp?: string       # ISO 8601 upload time
```

```mdl
type BackendDescriptor
  desc: |
    UI-facing descriptor for a registered storage option. Carries no upload/read behavior itself —
    that lives in the matching `BlobBackend` registered on the ECHO Hypergraph under `storage`.
  fields:
    id: string                # stable backend id (e.g. 'inline', 'wnfs', 'edge'); used as the settings key
    name: string               # display label shown in settings
    description?: string       # description shown next to the backend in settings
    storage: string             # Blob.fromBytes's `storage` option to use when this descriptor is selected
```

```mdl
type Settings
  desc: Per-user plugin settings stored in the ECHO space.
  fields:
    backend?: string         # active backend id; defaults to 'inline'
```

## Components

```mdl
component FilePreview
  desc: |
    Renders a File object using the appropriate HTML element for its MIME type.
    Images use <img>, videos use <video controls>, PDFs use <iframe>, and
    all other types fall back to a download link.
  props:
    type: string             # MIME type
    url: string              # renderable data:, blob:, or http(s): URL
  layout: |
    ┌──────────────────────────────┐
    │  <img> / <video> / <iframe>  │
    │  or [Download file] link     │
    └──────────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component FileInput
  desc: Drag-and-drop / browse file picker used inside the Create Object form.
  props:
    schema: Schema           # effect/Schema with UploadAnnotation on the file field
  emits:
    onChange(file: File)
  layout: |
    ┌──────────────────────────────┐
    │  [ Drop file or click here ] │
    └──────────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component FileSettings
  desc: Plugin settings panel rendered in the Composer settings surface.
  props:
    settings: Settings
  emits:
    onSettingsChange(settings: Settings)
  layout: |
    ┌──────────────────────────────┐
    │  Storage backend: [select ▼] │
    │  (one row per registered     │
    │   BackendDescriptor)         │
    └──────────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component FileArticle
  desc: |
    Full-viewport article container rendered for article, section, and slide
    roles. Loads the File's referenced Blob and resolves a renderable URL via
    Blob.url; if the backend has no getUrl, falls back to Blob.read and
    constructs a blob: object URL (revoked on unmount). Delegates to
    FilePreview. Shows an empty state while the URL is resolving or if the
    File is not attached to a database.
  props:
    role: AppSurface.Role
    subject: File
  layout: |
    ┌──────────────────────────────┐
    │                              │
    │      FilePreview             │
    │      (fills container)       │
    │                              │
    └──────────────────────────────┘
```

## Operations

```mdl
op Create
  key: org.dxos.plugin.file.operation.create
  desc: |
    Validates a browser File object's MIME type, resolves the active
    BackendDescriptor, and composes File.fromBytes (which hashes/uploads the
    bytes via the Blob API and adds the resulting Blob to the database) to
    construct a File ECHO object. Does not add the File object itself to the
    space — callers do that separately.
  input:
    file: BrowserFile        # browser File (globalThis.File)
    db: Database
  output: { object: File }
  errors:
    UnsupportedFileTypeError: MIME type is not image/*, video/*, or application/pdf
    FileTooLargeError: file exceeds the 4 MB inline limit (only possible when the
      resolved backend's storage is 'inline'; other backends scale beyond it)
    NoBackendError: no BackendDescriptor capability is registered
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: File upload

  req F-1.1: Accepted MIME types MUST be image/* (jpg, jpeg, png, gif, webp, svg),
    video/* (mp4, webm, mov), and application/pdf only.

  req F-1.2: Maximum upload size MUST be 4 MB when the resolved backend's storage
    is 'inline'. Other backends (e.g. edge, wnfs) are not subject to this cap.

  req F-1.3:
    when: user submits the Create Object form with a valid file
    then:
      - op:Create is invoked with the selected file and active database
      - the resulting File object is added to the space via SpaceOperation.AddObject
      - FileUploader capability returns metadata to the caller (name, type, and a
        renderable url resolved via Blob.url, if one is available)

  req F-1.4:
    when: file MIME type is not accepted
    then: UnsupportedFileTypeError returned; no ECHO write occurs

  req F-1.5:
    when: file size exceeds the limit and the resolved backend's storage is 'inline'
    then: FileTooLargeError returned; no ECHO write occurs
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Backend capability system

  req F-2.1: Any plugin may contribute a BackendDescriptor capability. Multiple
    descriptors may be registered simultaneously.

  req F-2.2: The inline BackendDescriptor MUST always be registered by FilePlugin
    itself, mapping to Blob's built-in 'inline' storage (bytes embedded on the
    Blob object; no separate BlobBackend registration needed).

  req F-2.3: The active backend is determined by Settings.backend. If the
    configured id is absent or unrecognised, the inline backend is used.

  req F-2.4: A BackendDescriptor's `storage` names the Blob storage used by
    File.fromBytes; the actual upload/read/getUrl implementation lives in a
    separate `BlobBackend` registered on the ECHO Hypergraph (via
    `client.graph.registerBlobBackend`), typically by the same plugin that
    contributes the descriptor (e.g. plugin-wnfs, or `@dxos/client` itself for
    'edge'). FilePlugin's descriptor and the Hypergraph's BlobBackend registry
    are independent — a descriptor with no matching registered backend fails at
    upload time with a `backend-not-registered` error, not at settings-selection time.
```

```mdl
feat F-3: File preview

  req F-3.1: FileArticle MUST resolve a renderable URL via Blob.url before
    rendering FilePreview. For inline files this is always a data: URL
    (constructed synchronously from the stored bytes, no Blob.read needed). For
    external files with no registered getUrl, FileArticle falls back to
    Blob.read and constructs a blob: URL, revoked on unmount.

  req F-3.2: FilePreview MUST render the appropriate element for each MIME class:
    image/* → <img>, video/* → <video controls>, application/pdf → <iframe>,
    other → <a download>.

  req F-3.3: FileArticle surfaces are registered for article, section,
    and slide roles so files embed correctly in Markdown and Presenter layouts.
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Markdown integration

  req F-4.1: A Markdown extension contributed at MarkdownEvents.SetupExtensions
    MUST allow files to be embedded in Markdown documents as inline attachments,
    resolving each embedded File's Blob URL the same way as FileArticle (Blob.url,
    falling back to Blob.read + blob: URL).
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Settings

  req F-5.1: The Settings panel MUST list all registered BackendDescriptor
    capabilities with their id, display name, and optional description.

  req F-5.2: Selecting a backend MUST persist the choice to Settings.backend
    via the SettingsAtom capability.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Upload image inline
  given: only the inline BackendDescriptor is registered
  when: user uploads a 1 MB PNG via the Create Object form
  then:
    - op:Create returns a File whose data Ref resolves to a Blob with data._tag === 'inline'
    - File.type === 'image/png', File.size === byte count
    - File is added to the space
```

```mdl
test T-2: Reject oversized file
  given: inline backend selected, 4 MB limit
  when: user uploads a 5 MB JPEG
  then:
    - FileTooLargeError is returned
    - no File object is created
    - no ECHO write occurs
```

```mdl
test T-3: Reject unsupported MIME type
  given: inline backend registered
  when: user uploads a .zip file
  then:
    - UnsupportedFileTypeError is returned
    - no File object is created
```

```mdl
test T-4: Preview inline image
  given: a File whose data Ref resolves to a Blob with data._tag === 'inline' and type === 'image/png'
  when: FileArticle is rendered
  then:
    - Blob.url resolves a data: URL synchronously from the Blob's bytes (no Blob.read call)
    - FilePreview renders an <img> element with that URL
```

```mdl
test T-5: Preview PDF
  given: a File with type === 'application/pdf' and a Blob resolved to an HTTP or data URL
  when: FilePreview is rendered
  then: an <iframe> element is rendered with the file URL as src
```

```mdl
test T-6: Backend fallback to inline
  given: Settings.backend is 'wnfs' but no BackendDescriptor with id 'wnfs' is registered
  when: op:Create is invoked
  then: the inline backend is used and the file is stored inline
```

```mdl
test T-7: External blob resolved via a registered BlobBackend's getUrl
  given: a File whose data Ref resolves to a Blob with data._tag === 'external' and a
    BlobBackend registered on the ECHO Hypergraph that resolves the Blob's URI scheme
    and implements getUrl
  when: FileArticle is rendered
  then:
    - Blob.url calls the registered backend's getUrl and resolves Some(url)
    - FilePreview receives the resolved renderable URL
    - Blob.read is never called
```

```mdl
test T-8: External blob without getUrl falls back to reading bytes
  given: a File whose data Ref resolves to an external Blob whose registered
    BlobBackend implements get but not getUrl
  when: FileArticle is rendered
  then:
    - Blob.url resolves None
    - Blob.read is called to fetch the bytes
    - a blob: object URL is created from the bytes and revoked on unmount
```

```mdl
test T-9: No backend error
  given: no BackendDescriptor capability is registered
  when: op:Create is invoked
  then: NoBackendError is returned
```

---

## Appendix: Extension Definitions

```mdl
ext type
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0
  desc: A named data structure with typed fields and optional literals.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    fields?: FieldMap
    literals?: UnionList
    extends?: TypeRef[]
```

```mdl
ext feat
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0
  desc: A named feature grouping one or more requirements.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    req: RequirementList
  nesting: self
```

```mdl
ext test
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0
  desc: An acceptance scenario expressed as given / when / then steps.
  fields:
    given?: Step | Step[]
    when?: Step | Step[]
    then: Step | Step[]
    tags?: TagList
```

```mdl
ext component
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0
  desc: A UI component with props, internal state, slots, actions, and events.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    props?: FieldMap
    state?: FieldMap
    slots?: FieldMap
    actions?: ActionMap
    emits?: EventMap
    layout?: CodeBlock
```

```mdl
ext op
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0
  desc: A named operation with typed inputs, outputs, and declared errors.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    input?: FieldMap
    output?: TypeExpr
    errors?: ErrorMap
    effects?: EffectList
    requires?: ServiceList
    note?: Prose
```
